Class Differ

  • java.lang.Object
    • Differ

  • public class Differ
extends java.lang.Object
    This class performs the diffing algorithm described in the paper: http://ilpubs.stanford.edu:8090/115/1/1995-46.pdf

      • findPosition

        private java.lang.Integer findPosition(CustomElement node)
        Find the position at which the rightNode has to be inserted / moved. The numbers refer to the second function in figure 9 of the paper
        Parameters:
        node - The node in the right tree
        Returns:
        The position to which the new rightNode has to be added / moved in the left tree

      • updateNodeAttributes

        private void updateNodeAttributes(CustomElement leftNode,
                                  CustomElement rightNode)
                           throws java.lang.Exception
        This function performs the diff algorithm as explained in the paper, only on the HTML attributes, not on the whole object. The AttributeDiffer also uses the StyleDiffer to diff styles explicitly
        Parameters:
        leftNode - the old node
        rightNode - the new node
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - This exception is thrown when a malformed EditAction is created

      • matchRecursively

        private void matchRecursively(CustomElement l,
                              CustomElement r)
                       throws java.lang.Exception
        Add two equal nodes to the matches. This function is called when a node is inserted: The inserted node is cloned to this.left, and children are matched
        Parameters:
        l - The newly inserted node
        r - The matching node in this.right
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception - When !l.equals(r) or l doesn't have the same number of children as r, an exception is thrown
